  "elapsed_s": 7.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "As this person came, as this rabbi came, you paid with whatever arrangements it was.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But it was more of a benevolent way, rather than a 'you owe me' type of way.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It was a way of paying-- same way of paying-- but it was done in a more [NON-ENGLISH] way in those days.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We were not Orthodox.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were very [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] tuned-- we were very tuned to our heritage, but we were not what I would call Hasidic, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] very religious Jews.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We played it out as a-- as-- as a very close Jewish-- Jewish family.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Since I was not privy, at the time, to know how another, more stringent, Jew would live, or I would say one that was more in the Hasidic, or the more restricted Jewish tradition, we-- I thought that-- now, as I look back, I thought we were very good Jews.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And so-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] I remember, when there was a death, people would just normally come right around for the [NON-ENGLISH] and for the prayers.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I remember when there was services to be had, people would get together in homes and-- it wasn't so much going to temples, because it was done on a more communal, more convenient basis, where there was-- like, in our complex, there was a lot of men, so they sort of formed their own congregations and sort of davened on their own.",
      "word_count": 63
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they were quite astute in the-- in the presentation of it, so-- I don't recall going to temple, per se, as we do here.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
